Claims CLAIMS We Claim: 1. An apparatus, comprising: at least one processor; and at least one memory comprising computer program code, the at least one memory and computer program code configured, with the at least one processor, to cause the apparatus at least to receive or retrieve load statistics for one or more distributed units; evaluate the load statistics to identify at least one highly loaded distributed unit from the one or more distributed units; identify at least one crowded beam in the at least one highly loaded distributed unit; and trigger the at least one highly loaded distributed unit to deactivate the at least one crowded beam. 2. The apparatus according to claim 1, wherein the load statistics comprise beam-load related measurement and statistics collected from the distributed units, wherein the beam-load related measurement and statistics comprise at least one of a number of active user equipment per beam or key quality indicators of the user equipment. 3. The apparatus according to claims 1 or 2, wherein one or more of the evaluating, identifying, and triggering is performed by a cell beam manager. 4. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-3, wherein the evaluating comprises determining one or more highly loaded distributed units from the received load statistics. 5. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-4, wherein the at least one crowded beam comprises beams that are serving a highest number of user equipment from among the beams in the distributed units for which load statistics have been received. 6. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-5, wherein the at least one memory and computer program code are configured, with the at least one processor, to cause the apparatus at least to identify whether candidate beams are available to carry additional user equipment to be offloaded from the at least one crowded beam. 7. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-6, wherein the at least one candidate beam comprises at least one of other beams in the at least one highly loaded distributed unit or beams in neighboring distributed units or cells. 8. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-7, wherein the triggering occurs when one or more candidate beams are identified as being available. 9. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-8, wherein the deactivation of the at least one crowded beam blocks new user equipment from connecting to the at least one crowded beam or causes user equipment already connected to the at least one crowded beam to find alternative beams. 10. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-9, wherein the at least one memory and computer program code are configured, with the at least one processor, to cause the apparatus at least to manage one or more beams of the distributed units. 11. The apparatus according to any of claims 1-10, wherein the at least one memory and computer program code are configured, with the at least one processor, to cause the apparatus at least to collect statistics on one or more beams of the distributed units. 12. An apparatus, comprising: means for receiving or retrieving load statistics for one or more distributed units; means for evaluating the load statistics to identify at least one highly loaded distributed unit from the one or more distributed units; means for identifying at least one crowded beam in the at least one highly loaded distributed unit; and means for triggering the at least one highly loaded distributed unit to deactivate the at least one crowded beam. 13. The apparatus according to claim 12, wherein the load statistics comprise beam-load related measurement and statistics collected from the distributed units, wherein the beam-load related measurement and statistics comprise at least one of a number of active user equipment per beam or key quality indicators of the user equipment. 14. The apparatus according to claims 12 or 13, wherein the apparatus comprises a cell beam manager. 15. The apparatus according to any of claims 12-14